{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981440515,"sessionID":"ses_1cc7b5445ffebHCo1A8zDVvtFb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_01Y5FVy2AgLx3PLXTNwXC4Jn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+## Issue 31969 design pattern notes\n+\n+- Scope: existing molecular_function oxidoreductase activity terms only.\n+- No new terms were created.\n+- No logical definitions (`intersection_of`) were added or changed.\n+- Primary pattern applied: catalytic activity terms should align asserted parentage with the mapped EC subclass and should use reaction-style text definitions that match the corresponding RHEA reaction when available.\n+- Label/definition updates were limited to cases called out in the issue where the existing label or text definition conflicted with the EC/RHEA classification.\n+\n+## Precedent consulted\n+\n+- Oxidoreductase parent classes in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+  - `GO:0016614`, `GO:0016616`, `GO:0016628`\n+  - `GO:0016645`\n+  - `GO:0016702`, `GO:0016706`, `GO:0016708`, `GO:0016709`, `GO:0016713`, `GO:0016717`\n+  - `GO:0016725`, `GO:0016726`\n+  - `GO:0050498`\n+- Existing reaction terms in the same branch already follow the pattern `Catalysis of the reaction: ...` with RHEA and/or EC support.\n+\n+## Curation decision summary\n+\n+- Use the EC subclass to choose the asserted `is_a` parent.\n+- Use RHEA reaction wording for definitions when the issue requested a RHEA-aligned update.\n+- Avoid broader structural changes beyond the misparented terms named in the issue.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+## Issue 31969 research notes\n+\n+- No external literature search was required for this batch.\n+- The issue body already specified the intended EC subclasses and replacement reaction definitions.\n+- The affected GO terms already carried EC and/or RHEA xrefs matching the requested corrections, so the work here was a consistency cleanup of parentage and selected labels/definitions.\n+- New PMIDs were not introduced.\n+- PMID validation was therefore N/A for this change set.\n+\n+## Sources used\n+\n+- Imported issue context in `__issue_context__.json`\n+- Existing EC and RHEA xrefs already present on the affected GO terms in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+## Issue 31969 design pattern notes\n+\n+- Scope: existing molecular_function oxidoreductase activity terms only.\n+- No new terms were created.\n+- No logical definitions (`intersection_of`) were added or changed.\n+- Primary pattern applied: catalytic activity terms should align asserted parentage with the mapped EC subclass and should use reaction-style text definitions that match the corresponding RHEA reaction when available.\n+- Label/definition updates were limited to cases called out in the issue where the existing label or text definition conflicted with the EC/RHEA classification.\n+\n+## Precedent consulted\n+\n+- Oxidoreductase parent classes in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`:\n+  - `GO:0016614`, `GO:0016616`, `GO:0016628`\n+  - `GO:0016645`\n+  - `GO:0016702`, `GO:0016706`, `GO:0016708`, `GO:0016709`, `GO:0016713`, `GO:0016717`\n+  - `GO:0016725`, `GO:0016726`\n+  - `GO:0050498`\n+- Existing reaction terms in the same branch already follow the pattern `Catalysis of the reaction: ...` with RHEA and/or EC support.\n+\n+## Curation decision summary\n+\n+- Use the EC subclass to choose the asserted `is_a` parent.\n+- Use RHEA reaction wording for definitions when the issue requested a RHEA-aligned update.\n+- Avoid broader structural changes beyond the misparented terms named in the issue.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+## Issue 31969 research notes\n+\n+- No external literature search was required for this batch.\n+- The issue body already specified the intended EC subclasses and replacement reaction definitions.\n+- The affected GO terms already carried EC and/or RHEA xrefs matching the requested corrections, so the work here was a consistency cleanup of parentage and selected labels/definitions.\n+- New PMIDs were not introduced.\n+- PMID validation was therefore N/A for this change set.\n+\n+## Sources used\n+\n+- Imported issue context in `__issue_context__.json`\n+- Existing EC and RHEA xrefs already present on the affected GO terms in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+## Issue 31969 design pattern notes\n+\n+- Scope: existing molecular_function oxidoreductase activity terms only.\n+- No new terms were created.\n+- No logical definitions (`intersection_of`) were added or changed.\n+- Primary pattern applied: catalytic activity terms should align asserted parentage with the mapped EC subclass and should use reaction-style text definitions that match the corresponding RHEA reaction when available.\n+- Label/definition updates were limited to cases called out in the issue where the existing label or text defin